The paper proposes a knowledge-enhanced graph neural network for multi-paragraph reasoning in open-domain question answering. This work involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are commonly associated with the computer science sub-categories of CL (Computation and Language), AI (Artificial Intelligence), and LG (Learning). The use of knowledge graphs and relational facts also suggests a connection to the sub-categories of IR (Information Retrieval) and DB (Databases). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.IR and cs.DB.
